100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 20, 1925, the aftermath of the Great Mississippi Flood of 1927 continues to dominate discussions, with local governments grappling with recovery and reconstruction efforts. In Europe, tensions rise as the League of Nations addresses the ongoing instability in the Rhineland following the Treaty of Versailles. Meanwhile, in the United States, a surge in automobile manufacturing is noted, as Ford and General Motors report record production rates amid a booming economy.
